## [function __libboks\.get\_button\_state__\(\)](#function-__libboksget_button_state__) {#function-__libboksget_button_state__}

Checks which buttons are currently pressed.

__Example:__

~~~ .python
l = exp.boks.get_button_state()
if 1 in l:
        print('Button 1 is pressed')
~~~

__Returns:__

A list of buttons that are currently pressed.

- Type: list

</div>

